W. A. CARPENTER, Inc., Plaintiff in Error, v. OAKLAND MOTOR CAR COMPANY, Defendant in Error. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 20, 1928. No. 151. Whalen, Murphy, McNamee & Creble, of Albany, N. Y. (Robert E. Whalen and Charles E. Nichols, Jr., both of Albany, N. Y., of counsel), for plaintiff in error. John T. Smith, of New York City (Frank A. Gaynor, of New York City, of counsel), for defendant in error.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed in •open court.
